<p>
	Cardamom essential oil is well known for its use in sensual or aphrodisiac blends including massages, bath oils or for room fragrancing.</p>
<p>
	It is also renowned for easing nausea, digestive problems, wind and heartburn. It can be used as a bath oil and is especially good in winter for colds and chills or massaged into the stomach and upper body when blended with a carrier oil.</p>
<p>
	The therapeutic properties of cardamom oil include antiseptic, antispasmodic, carminative, cephalic, digestive, diuretic, expectorant, stimulant, stomachic and tonic.</p>
<p>
	Aroma: cardamom is a warm, aromatic herb having a distinctively strong aroma that is sweet, spicy and almost balsamic in fragrance with uplifting and invigorating properties. Note: cardamom essential oil has a strong aroma and should be used in moderation. &copy; Please do not copy text. Avena product description &ndash; Cardamom Essential Oil (Elettaria cardamomum).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
